The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, January 20, 2003 				 Conversion
																								Mysore, Jan. 19 (PTI): BJP MLA A. Ramdas, along with 20 party and VHP activists, was taken into custody today as they were offering dharna in front of a police station here to protest the alleged conversion activities of members of a Christian organisation, police said.																								There was tension around a hotel as Bajrang Dal and VHP activists stormed into a room and questioned the members of the organisation on their attempts to convert Hindus into Christianity. The police arrested four activists. 																								The activists alleged that the police were adopting double standards and sat on dharna.
